sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I2048
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Positive and negative feedback regulated T7 RNAP expression system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is an intermediate version of a biological virtual machine. T7 RNAP expression is controlled by a T7 promoter, forming a positive feedback loop or autogene. LacI expression is controlled by the same promoter. The promoter is repressible by LacI leading to negative feedback. The combination of positive and negative feedback should lead to a moderate, stable level of T7 RNAP in the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Based on and developed from a system built by Bill Studier at Brookhaven National Labs

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I2044
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Double protein generator (T7 RNAP and LacI)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LacI and T7 RNAP are transcribed polycistronically and translation of both is regulated by B0032. A T7 terminator is downstream. This part is being used in the construction of VM2.0
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I2034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This protein generator is composed of an E. coli RBS, a lacI coding region and a T7 terminator. It is designed for use with a T7 promoter but should be functional with a E. coli promoter also. Ultimately, it will be used in an early version of a virtual machine.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: B0032 is a very reliable RBS and B0016 is the T7 terminator

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_R0184
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A mutant version of the T7lac promoter designed by Dubendorff and Studier. The promoter is based on the strong ??10 T7 promoter but incorporates an A->C mutation at -16. The LacI operator site is a partially symmetric 25bp sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bartholomew Canton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is based on the T7lac promoter described by Dubendorff and Studier (JMB 1991, 219, 45-59). The only modification is the mutation at -16.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The -16 mutation was included to weaken the consensus promoter as described by Imburgio and co-workers (see BBa_R0183 for more information)
